result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany D. Eldridge was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Brittany D. Eldridge is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Brittany D. Eldridge was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Brittany D. Eldridge was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Brittany D. Eldridge was found guilty of Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Brittany D. Eldridge in court with attorney Zachary Glascock.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases called 10CF94 and 14CF99.   Case 10CF94 called first.  Matter is on for expungement hearing.  Court reviews file.   Court will expunge, court finds def has completed sentence.  14CF99 Ct 1 amended to possess Drug para not as repeater.  Ct 2 dismissed.  Ct 3 amended to delete 2nd offence as repeater.  Ct 4 plea.  Sentence withheld, probation .  Court will dismiss Ct 2.  Ct 1 amended delete repeater, misdemeanor - No contest plea entered.  Ct 3 - amended to possession of THC - misdemeanor - No contest plea entered.  Ct 4 - No contest plea entered.  Court reviews plea questionnaire.  Constitutiuonal rights and right to jury trial reviewed.  Court finds pleas accepted.  Facts set forth in criminal complaint.  Court finds factual basis and enters judgment.  Nothing by def.  Court will accept plea agreement.  Sentence withheld, probation 18 month on each count.  AODA and follow through  Court cost on each count.  Bond to be applied to cost.    If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.
